body:
Verilator version tried: 5.016.

Let's say I have C:
```
typedef struct {
  int f1;
  int f2;
} thing_t;
```
and SV:
```
typedef struct {
  int f1;
  int f2;
} thing_t;

import "DPI-C" function int do_thing(thing_t thing);
```

Verilator doesn't swallow this, saying:
`error: cannot convert ‘blah__DOT__thing_t__struct__0’ to ‘IData’`

I can work around it by making the SV struct `packed`, but then the fields come across in reverse order, so I've effectively ended up with (minus expletives):
```
// Structs have to be 'packed' for v e rilator.
// This means the order of members is REVERSED w.r.t their C declaration.
typedef struct packed {
  int f2;
  int f1;
} thing_t;
```
